<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9800 - MAINTENANCE - CHECKING AND FILLING CAB
        TILT HYDRAULIC SYSTEM
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="pm" graphiccount="1">
        <title>CHECKING AND FILLING CAB TILT HYDRAULIC SYSTEM</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate filler plug on lift pump reservoir (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601809">Item 2, Figure 9</hotlnk>). Remove and check fluid level with the cab in the
                down position (to prevent overfilling). Oil should be up to the bottom of the filler plug well. Fill as
                required with Dexron Automatic Transmission Fluid. DO NOT USE BRAKE FLUID.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1601809" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1601809" filename="../figg16/g1601809.png" type="png" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 9. Cab Tilt Hydraulic System</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. PUMP HANDLE RECEPTACLE</callout1>
                <callout1>2. RESERVOIR FILL PLUG</callout1>
                <callout1>3. LIFT CONTROL LEVER (RAISE POSITION)</callout1>
                <callout1>4. CONTROL BUTTON (AIR ASSIST)</callout1>
                <callout1>5. FITTING FOR ATTACHING EXTERNAL AIR</callout1>
                <callout1>6. AIR PUMP MOTOR</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the cab lift pump is repaired or replaced prior to connecting the hoses, it should be
                filled with oil and while the RAISE- LOWER lever is in each position, stroke the pump to purge all of
                the air from the pump. After installation of the pump assembly, check the pump operation. The hydraulic
                lift system will have to be bled. Refer to BLEEDING CAB TILT HYDRAULIC SYSTEM, below.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <important>
                <para>To prevent overfilling, do not refill reservoir ith cab in raised position.</para>
            </important>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
